sub_title: MSc Biology graduate pursuing PhD in behavioral ecology of vertebrates
summary: My academic ambition is to put my knowledge and skills to work in applied behavioral and ecological research for the benefit of mitigating human-animal conflicts and aiding conservation efforts. I am versatile, pragmatic, and have a wide range of knowledge covering many subjects other than my formal academic training. I excel at analyzing problems diagnostically, and thinking outside the box. My priority above working hard is working intellectually and efficiently.
